Let's talk about gratitude.

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:15.040
And to begin, I'd like to
emphasize the various aspects

00:09:15.040 --> 00:09:16.250
of mental and physical health

00:09:16.250 --> 00:09:17.650
that have been shown to benefit

00:09:17.650 --> 00:09:19.890
from a regular gratitude practice.

00:09:19.890 --> 00:09:20.810
There are studies showing

00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:25.460
that performing a gratitude
practice twice or three times,

00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:28.560
or even just once a week,
can lead to a pervasive,

00:09:28.560 --> 00:09:32.814
a long lasting impact
on subjective wellbeing.

00:09:32.814 --> 00:09:35.910
People report feeling
happier, more meaning, joy,

00:09:35.910 --> 00:09:38.610
even awe for their life experience,

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:41.470
simply in response to
adding a gratitude practice.

00:09:41.470 --> 00:09:43.760
The key thing is it has to be
the right gratitude practice.

00:09:43.760 --> 00:09:44.640
And we're going to talk about

00:09:44.640 --> 00:09:46.522
what the right gratitude
practice looks like

00:09:46.522 --> 00:09:48.350
in just a little bit.

00:09:48.350 --> 00:09:51.675
But there are additional
benefits of a gratitude practice.

00:09:51.675 --> 00:09:56.200
There are studies showing that
a regular gratitude practice

00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:59.750
can provide resilience
to trauma, in two ways;

00:09:59.750 --> 00:10:01.720
it can provide a reframing

00:10:01.720 --> 00:10:04.270
and resilience to prior
traumatic experiences.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:05.220
So buffering people

00:10:05.220 --> 00:10:07.890
against the negative physiological effects

00:10:07.890 --> 00:10:10.060
and psychological effects
of earlier trauma,

00:10:10.060 --> 00:10:13.010
but also inoculating them in many ways

00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:16.020
to any traumas that might
arrive later in life.

00:10:16.020 --> 00:10:17.700
So that's a powerful thing.

00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:19.340
And today we will talk about

00:10:19.340 --> 00:10:20.600
how that's actually accomplished.

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:23.310
It's actually accomplished
by shifting the way

00:10:23.310 --> 00:10:25.290
that the fear and defense networks

00:10:25.290 --> 00:10:27.390
in the brain actually function.

